chunks.html_content: Crimes committed against someone because of their disability, transgender-identity, race, religion or belief, or sexual orientation are hate crimes and should be reported to the police.
chunks.plain_content:
Report hate crime
Crimes committed against someone because of their disability, transgender-identity, race, religion or belief, or sexual orientation are hate crimes and should be reported to the police.

chunks.html_content:
Hate crimes can include:

  • threatening behaviour
  • assault
  • robbery
  • damage to property
  • inciting others to commit hate crimes
  • harassment
  • online abuse

You can report hate crime online.

chunks.html_content: Call 999 if you’re reporting a crime that’s in progress or if someone is in immediate danger.
chunks.plain_content:

Call 999 if you’re reporting a crime that’s in progress or if someone is in immediate danger.

chunks.html_content:
If the crime isn’t an emergency, call 101 or contact your local police.
